[bleep], [bleep], [bleep].

36:58.175 --> 36:59.716
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

37:03.305 --> 37:05.138
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

37:05.265 --> 37:06.723
- Welcome back, bladesmiths.

37:06.850 --> 37:08.225
You've had five days
at your home forge

37:08.352 --> 37:10.310
to work on your Koras.

37:10.437 --> 37:12.604
Josh, why don't you tell us
a little bit about your Kora?

37:12.731 --> 37:15.565
- Well, I decided to build
a Damascus Kora.

37:15.692 --> 37:17.692
<i> I did an all-steel handle,</i>
<i> all-steel construction.</i>

37:17.819 --> 37:20.612
<i> That's what I found</i>
<i> the originals to be.</i>

37:20.739 --> 37:22.447
<i> I'm pretty proud of it.</i>
<i> It was a good week.</i>

37:22.574 --> 37:24.407
- Great. Liam?

37:24.534 --> 37:26.618
- Yeah, I had a blast making it,
and I did a lot of research.

37:26.745 --> 37:28.370
<i> I found</i>
<i> that it's supposed to be</i>

37:28.497 --> 37:29.829
<i> a really heavy chopping knife,</i>

37:29.957 --> 37:31.456
<i> so that's what</i>
<i> I tried to give to you</i>

37:31.583 --> 37:33.625
<i> and still put</i>
<i> my own style to it.</i>

37:33.752 --> 37:36.461
- Fantastic.
Both weapons look amazing,

37:36.588 --> 37:38.421
but as we all know,
it's all about

37:38.548 --> 37:40.215
how they hold up
in our weapons tests.

37:40.342 --> 37:42.467
First up
is the sharpness test.

37:42.594 --> 37:44.594
Doug?

37:44.721 --> 37:48.306
- The Nepalese Kora was a blade
that had a distinct inward curve

37:48.433 --> 37:50.016
with a spatulated flare
at the tip,

37:50.143 --> 37:52.477
making it a weapon
for slicing and chopping.

37:52.604 --> 37:54.479
I will cut
across these sandbags.

37:54.606 --> 37:56.606
Let's see how sharp
your blades are.

37:56.733 --> 37:57.649
Josh, you're up first.
You ready?

37:57.776 --> 38:00.026
- I'm ready.
Let's do it.

38:00.153 --> 38:07.075
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

38:16.211 --> 38:18.044
- Josh, great balance.

38:18.171 --> 38:21.006
The blade really wants
to chop and slice.

38:21.133 --> 38:23.133
The recovery of the blade
makes it one

38:23.260 --> 38:25.677
that wants to continue
for combat.

38:25.804 --> 38:27.887
One problem I have here
is this handle.

38:28.015 --> 38:29.306
It tends to roll.

38:29.433 --> 38:31.975
But other than that,
it will cut.

38:32.102 --> 38:33.685
Good job, sir.
- Thank you.

38:33.812 --> 38:34.728
Liam, you're up next.
Are you ready?

38:34.855 --> 38:35.979
- Yeah.

38:36.106 --> 38:43.028
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

38:50.329 --> 38:51.911
- When you said
that this was heavy,

38:52.039 --> 38:52.954
you weren't kidding.

38:53.081 --> 38:54.372
This is a chopper.

38:54.499 --> 38:56.916
A little hard to control
on the recoil,

38:57.044 --> 38:59.419
but not enough to where
I can't wield it.

38:59.546 --> 39:01.963
This, sir, will cut.

39:02.090 --> 39:04.132
- Great.
- Good job.

39:04.259 --> 39:05.759
Next up is the strength test.

39:05.886 --> 39:07.427
Dave?

39:07.554 --> 39:09.846
- Gentlemen, to test
the strength of your Kora,

39:09.973 --> 39:13.224
I'm gonna take one blow
into these skulls.

39:13.352 --> 39:14.851
Josh, you're up.
You ready?

39:14.978 --> 39:17.020
- I'm ready.
- All right, fantastic.

39:17.147 --> 39:24.069
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

39:30.118 --> 39:32.035
- Nice.

39:32.162 --> 39:34.329
- Josh, it went
right into the skull.

39:34.456 --> 39:37.665
Swings easy,
super lightweight,

39:37.793 --> 39:39.793
but like Doug said,

39:39.920 --> 39:41.878
the handle wants to roll
in my hand.

39:42.005 --> 39:44.255
Nonetheless, nicely done.

39:44.383 --> 39:45.507
- Thank you.

39:45.634 --> 39:47.467
- All right, moving on.
You ready?

39:47.594 --> 39:49.803
- Yeah.
- Okay.

39:49.930 --> 39:52.097
<i> - I feel really</i>
<i> confident in my blade.</i>

39:52.224 --> 39:55.058
If Josh's can do it,
then mine will do it as well.

39:55.185 --> 40:02.148
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

40:04.444 --> 40:06.444
- Wow. It's a beast.

40:06.571 --> 40:08.071
[chuckles]

40:08.198 --> 40:09.406
It feels really nice
in the hand.

40:09.533 --> 40:11.449
You did a great job
on this handle.

40:11.576 --> 40:15.120
Obviously, we pretty much
took care of that skull.

40:15.247 --> 40:18.581
Now, this thing, once you
get it started, it's gonna go.

40:18.708 --> 40:21.501
- Right.
- My only worry is stopping it.

40:21.628 --> 40:22.794
- Yeah.
- You don't always have to have

40:22.921 --> 40:25.338
a heavy blade
to make a heavy blow.

40:25.465 --> 40:27.549
But it's a beautiful piece.
Nice job.

40:27.676 --> 40:29.467
- Thank you.
- Well done.

40:29.594 --> 40:31.177
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

40:31.304 --> 40:33.847
- Liam, Josh, the judges
have scrutinized

40:33.974 --> 40:36.474
every detail of your weapon,

40:36.601 --> 40:38.435
and they've made
their final decision.

40:38.562 --> 40:40.812
Before I announce
who that winner is,

40:40.939 --> 40:43.273
they have some things they'd
like to say to both of you.

40:43.400 --> 40:44.774
Jason?

40:44.901 --> 40:48.361
- Liam, your sword is
very impressive.

40:48.488 --> 40:50.780
<i> I love the appearance of it.</i>
<i> It was like an axe.</i>

40:50.907 --> 40:52.407
<i> I like to see</i>
<i> something like that,</i>

40:52.534 --> 40:54.909
<i>and I call it "phantasmagoric,"</i>
<i> you know?</i>

40:55.036 --> 40:58.246
<i> And it has the appearance</i>
<i>of, like, "This thing is death.</i>

40:58.373 --> 41:00.290
<i> See it and die."</i>

41:00.417 --> 41:03.251
You did a great job.
Very well done.

41:03.378 --> 41:05.044
- Thank you.

41:05.172 --> 41:06.504
- Josh, aside from your blade
performing very well

41:06.631 --> 41:08.214
on all the tests, the fullering

41:08.341 --> 41:11.468
<i> you did on the spine--</i>
<i> just pure eye candy.</i>

41:11.595 --> 41:14.846
<i> If ever there's one problem</i>
<i> I have here, is this handle.</i>

41:14.973 --> 41:16.931
<i> When I was using it,</i>
<i> it tends to roll,</i>

41:17.058 --> 41:18.516
but what you turned in

41:18.643 --> 41:20.810
is one of the most visually
stunning blades

41:20.937 --> 41:22.270
we've ever seen
in this Forge.

41:22.397 --> 41:23.438
- Thank you.

41:23.565 --> 41:25.190
- Gentlemen,

41:25.317 --> 41:28.026
both of your weapons
are spectacular,

41:28.153 --> 41:30.862
but in this competition,
there can only be one champion.

41:30.989 --> 41:32.113
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

41:32.240 --> 41:33.865
And that champion is...

41:33.992 --> 41:38.620
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

41:38.747 --> 41:40.705
Liam.
Congratulations.

41:40.832 --> 41:43.124
You are
the "Forged in Fire" champion.

41:43.251 --> 41:46.377
Josh, unfortunately,
your blade did not make the cut.

41:46.505 --> 41:48.338
Dave will explain.

41:48.465 --> 41:50.965
- Josh, we've never seen
two weapons so evenly matched,

41:51.092 --> 41:56.012
and our decision came down
to one incredibly small thing,

41:56.139 --> 41:58.473
and it was the fact that that
handle torqued in Doug's hand,

41:58.600 --> 41:59.974
torqued in mine.

42:00.101 --> 42:02.018
It's an amazing piece of work.

42:02.145 --> 42:03.895
You should be
incredibly proud of it.

42:04.022 --> 42:06.397
I mean,
I wish I could own it.

42:06.525 --> 42:09.400
- Josh, please
surrender your weapon.

42:09.528 --> 42:11.653
<i> - I came here</i>
<i> to challenge myself,</i>

42:11.780 --> 42:14.447
and I came here to hopefully
represent bladesmithing well,

42:14.574 --> 42:16.199
<i> and I think I did that.</i>

42:16.326 --> 42:18.243
I'm disappointed
in the judges' decision,

42:18.370 --> 42:20.745
<i> but I'm satisfied</i>
<i> with the Kora that I produced.</i>

42:20.872 --> 42:22.664
I'm going home to my kids,
which is where I'm happiest,

42:22.791 --> 42:24.332
<i> so that's where I want to be.</i>

42:24.459 --> 42:25.917
- Liam, congratulations.

42:26.044 --> 42:27.544
You are
the "Forged in Fire" champion

42:27.671 --> 42:30.588
and will be receiving a check
for ten grand. Good job.

42:30.715 --> 42:32.674
- You are our youngest
champion so far.

42:32.801 --> 42:34.425
Congratulations.
Great job.

42:34.553 --> 42:36.386
- Good job.

42:36.513 --> 42:38.221
<i> - I just won "Forged in Fire."</i>

42:38.348 --> 42:40.014
Just wow.

42:40.141 --> 42:42.183
<i> This is a big feat for me</i>
<i> to accomplish</i>

42:42.310 --> 42:44.227
<i> against a Mastersmith.</i>

42:44.354 --> 42:46.604
I think that all the people
that I went to high school with,

42:46.731 --> 42:50.608
